title: Independent candidate Meena Khan wins PK-83 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Meena Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-83, Peshawar-XII by securing 38,117 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Awami National Party (ANP) candidate Samar Haroon Balour who bagged 33,500 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turnout remained 34.88 per cent.
